title: For Sale:  Trijicon TR24 1-4x, Red w/ LaRue QD mount
postcontent:
For sale: Trijicon TR24 1-4x, Red Triangle with LaRue SPR-1.5 QD mount 

This is a true 1-4x optic, very low distortion at 1x, works like a standard red dot. Up to 4x zoom makes shots in the 100-200yd range a breeze. Fiber optic is very bright even in low/evening light, has to be turned down in full sun. The only issue I have with it is the tritium is very weak by itself (total darkness). You can rig an LED to the fiber optic coil fairly easily if you're handy with electronics and want to shoot in the dark. I prefer a weapon light if I'm going to use something for home defense, anyway. This is not really a close quarters optic but a great all-around scope for 3-gun and hunting. 

The LaRue QD mount is rock solid and will retain zero after removal and re-mount. Awesome for cleaning and storage (just mark the rail you place it on). 

The scope retails between $800-900 and the mount usually runs $210 - 
Asking $700 for both. Comes with lens caps, original box and lens cleaner.

title: For Sale:  Bowtech Stryker Solution LS
postcontent:
I am well-aware that the internet is the last place one would look to for sympathy, and as such, please know that I am not looking for sympathy but rather, giving a little background so you know how little this crossbow was used and why it is being sold despite its excellent condition.
 My dad was feeling quite down and was having some medical issues; I wanted to cheer him up and offered to buy him anything he wanted for his upcoming birthday. He wanted a crossbow. He lived in Michigan and I have been here in Evansville for work and so we looked at crossbows at different stores and separate from one another. When we talked on the phone we discovered we both had the same bow in mind: the "Bowtech Diamond Stryker Solution LS". Admittedly, we both had chosen this bow for very different reasons; my dad chose it because he knew his stuff when it came to hunting, and I chose it because I know nothing and care nothing for hunting, but I like the show "The Walking Dead" and this is the type of crossbow Darryl uses to nail zombies between the eyes, though my dad preferred the camo version of this model over Darryl's black model.
 I scraped together most of the money and borrowed the rest. It really made my dad happy. He took it out the night before his procedure and shot a really big 8 point. The next afternoon he went in to the hospital and could not speak, though he was able to communicate through blinking in response to yes and no questions. That is how he was able to tell the nurse that no, he didn't know the stranger who was holding his hand (that was me) and no he did not wish to be kept alive by machines.
 It's been a year now, and rather than being a memorable token, seeing this crossbow against my wall just makes me sad, so I guess it's time to sell it. 
 The only flaw it has is that 1 arrow is missing as it completely passed through the deer and was never found.
 I will also include the Tarantula carrying case and extinguisher deer call with dvd that I had bought him for Christmas and never got a chance to give.
 I don't expect to get my money back, so I will be accepting the best offer I receive.

 Info from Strykerxbow.com:
 The Solution LS has everything you are looking for in a premium crossbow package. This bow is at the top of its class with Stryker's leading technology, enhanced safety features (including a grip shield and Cease-Fire secondary safety), and our brand new laminated limbs. The Solution LS features a brand new high efficiency cam system as well as redesigned safety features on this Luxury Series crossbow. Decorated in Realtree® APG® and with a bolt speed of 390 fps, it is sure to get the job done quickly! The Solution LS is everything you want in a crossbow, not just what you need.
 MSRP - $1,049 w/package
 Draw Weight -- 155lbs

title: For Sale:  Processed Lead for bullets or Fishing weights
postcontent:
Processed lead from tire weights.  
Tire weights are a great source for reloading bullets, because they have tin and antimony already mixed in.  There is no zinc in the lead.  Careful consideration is taken to keep the heat low enough to not exceed 780 degrees F. to not allow zinc to melt, and keep it out of the processed lead.  Right now I have a half ton ready to go.  Cash only, $1.50 per pound.  Special offers can be negotiated for bulk buys. can meet or be delivered North South or Metro Denver.

The VMAC 45 100 Series Pistol is a descendant of the famous Military Armament Corporation ( MAC 10 ) machine pistol manufactured in the early 1980's.  Like the MAC 10, these semi-automatic versions are made of a formed sheet metal lower receiver containing the trigger mechanism and square tube upper receiver, housing the barrel and bolt assembly.  The magazine well is incorporated in the pistol grip.  It uses the blow-back unlocked bolt design.  This weapon accepts modified grease gun mags and has a mag capacity of 30 rounds.  The barrel has an external thread of 7/8 'x 9 and accepts many aftermarket extensions and fake suppressors.  Fires the hard hitting and plentiful .45 ACP round.
